body:
### Describe the bug

I'm using the package quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache-kotlin to define multiple entities that should belong to different datasources. The classes are annotated with javax.persistence @Entity and @Column and extend the PanacheEntity class. I'm using the repository pattern to retrieve these entities. The application properties file defines multiple datasources and each one is mapped by a different peristence unit. Via rest calls these entities will then be queried. A complete example set up can be seen at https://github.com/boceckts/quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache-kotlin/tree/main/src/main.

The code worked on the latests 1.x version (1.13.7.Final) of quarkus but after upgrading to any quarkus 2.x (e.g. 2.3.0.Final or 2.2.1.Final) version I receive the Error `2021-10-19 21:45:01,952 [io.qua.ver.htt.run.QuarkusErrorHandler] (executor-thread-0) HTTP Request to /user failed, error id: c1b859cc-c60c-45cd-8c92-a3e27b34a1ae-8: org.jboss.resteasy.spi.UnhandledException: java.lang.IllegalStateException: No entities were found. Did you forget to annotate your Panache Entity classes with '@Entity'?`

Entities are defined like this:
```
@Entity(name = "userentity")
class UserEntity : PanacheEntity() {

    @Column(name = "name")
    lateinit var name: String

}

@Entity(name = "propertyentity")
class PropertyEntity : PanacheEntity() {

    @Column(name = "name")
    lateinit var name: String

}
```
Repositories like this:
```
@ApplicationScoped
class UserRepository: PanacheRepository<UserEntity>{

    fun findByName(name: String) = find("name", name).firstResult()

}

@ApplicationScoped
class PropertyRepository: PanacheRepository<UserEntity>{

    fun findByName(name: String) = find("name", name).firstResult()

}
```
The endpoints like this:
```
@Path("/user")
class UserResource(
        private val userRepository: UserRepository
) {

    @GET
    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
    fun hello() = "Hello User Resource ${userRepository.findByName("default")}"
}

@Path("/property")
class PropertyResource(
        private val propertyRepository: PropertyRepository
) {

    @GET
    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
    fun hello() = "Hello Property Resource ${propertyRepository.findByName("default")}"
}
```

And the configuration for the different datasources and persistence units like this:
```
# dev services with named persistence units
quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2
quarkus.datasource.devservices.enabled=false

quarkus.datasource.user.devservices.enabled=true
quarkus.datasource.user.db-kind=h2
quarkus.datasource.user.username=username1
quarkus.datasource.user.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:user
quarkus.datasource.user.jdbc.max-size=11

quarkus.datasource.property.devservices.enabled=true
quarkus.datasource.property.db-kind=h2
quarkus.datasource.property.username=username2
quarkus.datasource.property.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:property
quarkus.datasource.property.jdbc.max-size=12

# hibernate configuration
quarkus.hibernate-orm."property".datasource=property
quarkus.hibernate-orm."property".packages=org.acme.property.model

quarkus.hibernate-orm."user".datasource=user
quarkus.hibernate-orm."user".packages=org.acme.user.model
```

### Expected behavior

Works as in quarkus 1.x version, e.g. the defined panache entities are found for the different persistence units and I can retreive them from the database.

### Actual behavior

IllegalStateException occurs when entities are queries from the database saying `No entities were found. Did you forget to annotate your Panache Entity classes with '@Entity'?` even though the entites are annotated.

### How to Reproduce?

Reproduce by doing the following steps:

1. Checkout https://github.com/boceckts/quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache-kotlin
2. run `./mvnw compile quarkus:dev`
3. open browser at localhost:8080/user or localhost:8080/property

